Hovnanian Secured Debt Yields Soar to 18.5% After Exchange Offer

-- B y   S a p n a   M a h e s h w a r i
-- 
2011-09-30T15:10:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/hovnanian-secured-debt-yields-soar-to-18-5-after-exchange-offer.html
Hovnanian Enterprises Inc. (HOV) ’s senior
secured bonds are yielding 18.5 percent after the largest
homebuilder in  New Jersey  announced exchange offers for up to
$220 million of securities.   The company’s $797 million of 10.625 percent notes due in
October 2016 tumbled 4.4 cents to 75 cents on the dollar as of
10:31 a.m. in New York after a 5.3 cents drop yesterday,
according to Trace, the bond-price reporting system of the
Financial Industry Regulatory Authority. The debt was yielding
15 percent on Sept. 27, the data show.     The  Red Bank , New Jersey-based homebuilder is offering to
exchange senior notes with coupons ranging from 6.25 percent to
11.875 percent and maturities from 2014 through 2017 for up to
$220 million of new 2 percent senior secured bonds due 2021,
according to a statement distributed by Globe Newswire on Sept.
28. Hovnanian said the offer will expire on Oct. 26 and that the
early tender and consent time is at 5 p.m. in  New York  on Oct.
12.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Sapna Maheshwari in New York at 
